{
  "texts": [
    "We may not have explored all the possible combinations and variations of prompts that could potentially improve the performance of the clinical NLP tasks.",
    "Third, the LLMs do not release the details of the data set that they were trained on.",
    "Hence, the high accuracy could be because the models would have already seen the data during training and not because of the effectiveness of the prompts.",
    "Future WorkWe plan to address these challenges and limitations in our future work.",
    "We aim to develop more systematic and automated methods for prompt design and evaluation, such as using prompt-tuning or meta-learning techniques."
  ]
}